Chitchat App – Child Sexual Abuse and Exploitation (CSAE) Policy

At Chitchat, we uphold a strict zero-tolerance policy toward all forms of child sexual abuse and exploitation (CSAE). Protecting minors is a top priority, and we are committed to maintaining a safe and responsible digital environment for all users.

Our Commitment
Chitchat explicitly prohibits:

Content that depicts, promotes, or normalizes CSAE

Solicitation or grooming of minors

Sharing or distributing explicit material involving minors

Attempts to bypass child protection features or moderation

Enforcement Measures
We actively:

Monitor content using automated tools and human moderators

Remove and report any CSAE-related content immediately

Permanently ban users who violate child safety standards

Cooperate with legal authorities and law enforcement in all relevant cases

Report CSAE content to the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC)

Compliance
Chitchat complies with:

Google Play’s Developer Program Policies

The United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child (UNCRC)

All applicable local and international child protection laws

Reporting Concerns

If you encounter any content or behavior that violates our CSAE standards, please report it immediately to:

abuse@chitchatapp.com

We take all reports seriously and will respond as swiftly as possible.
